{"api_url": "http://quantmind.github.io/lux/jsonapi/docs/js/code", "html_url": "http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/js/code", "head": {}, "name": "js_code", "content_type": "text/html", "slug": "js/code", "html": {"main": "<section id=\"page-header\" class=\"page-header-outer js_code-header\">\n    <div class=\"layer\">\n        <div class=\"page-header\">\n            <div class=\"container fullpage\">\n                <div class=\"row fullpage\">\n                    <div class=\"col-sm-12 text-center\">\n                        <breadcrumbs></breadcrumbs>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>\n\n<div id=\"page-main\">\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"js_code-main col-md-12\">\n                <div class=\"center-block\" style=\"max-width: 900px\" data-highlight data-hash-scroll>\n                    <div class=\"section\" id=\"highlight\">\n<h1>highlight<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#highlight\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h1>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: <a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../api/ui#module-lux.extensions.ui\" title=\"lux.extensions.ui\"><tt class=\"xref py py-mod docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">lux.extensions.ui</span></tt></a>, <tt class=\"xref py py-mod docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">lux.extensions.code</span></tt></p>\n<p>AngularJs module for code highlighting using <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://highlightjs.org/\">highlightjs</a>. This angular module\nshould be used in conjunction with the <tt class=\"xref py py-mod docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">lux.extensions.code</span></tt> extentension.\nIn your config file add the extension to the list of <tt class=\"xref std std-setting docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">EXTENSIONS</span></tt> and\nspecify a theme:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-python\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre>EXTENSIONS = [\n    ...\n    &#39;lux.extensions.ui&#39;,\n    &#39;lux.extensions.code&#39;,\n    ...\n]\nCODE_HIGHLIGHT_THEME = &#39;github&#39;\n</pre></div>\n</div>\n<p>In Javascript you need to use the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">highlight</span></tt> directive on the outermost\nelement containing code to highlight:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-html\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span class=\"nt\">&lt;div</span> <span class=\"na\">data-highlight</span><span class=\"nt\">&gt;</span>\n...\n<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/div&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>\n</div>\n<p>The <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">highlight</span></tt> module containing the directive is added to lux modules to include in\nthe bootstrapping process by the <tt class=\"xref py py-mod docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">lux.extensions.code</span></tt> extension.</p>\n</div>\n\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n<div class='small hidden-print text-muted' id='page-footer'>\n    <div class='container'>\n        <div class='row'>\n            <div class='block col-sm-5'>\n                <div class='hidden-xs'>\n                    <ul class=\"fa-ul text-left\">\n    <li><i class=\"fa-li fa fa-copyright\"></i>2014 <a href=\"http://quantmind.com\">Quantmind</a></li>\n    <li>Site build with Lux on python 3.4.1</li>\n    <li>Docs build with <a href=\"http://sphinx-doc.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Sphinx</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/changelog\">Changelog</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/api/\">API</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/EXTENSIONS/\">Extensions</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/images\">Images</a></li>\n</ul>\n                </div>\n                <div class='text-center visible-xs'>\n                    <ul class=\"fa-ul text-left\">\n    <li><i class=\"fa-li fa fa-copyright\"></i>2014 <a href=\"http://quantmind.com\">Qu